   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Running REPET\n",
    "=============\n",
    "\n",
    "Introduction\n",
    "------------\n",
    "\n",
    "The REpeating Pattern Extraction Technique, or REPET, is source separation algorithm that separates a repeating\n",
    "\"background\" from a non-repeating \"foreground\". REPET finds the repeating period in an audio signal, slices the signal\n",
    "into \"frames\" of the same length of the repeating period and \"overlays\" those frames. Once the frames are overlayed,\n",
    "REPET extracts the non-repeating part by filtering out values that are far from the median value at each frame.\n",
    "\n",
    "In order to run REPET in *nussl*, we first must create an `AudioSignal` object. We're going to load a file as before.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Matching file found at /home/pseetharaman/.nussl/audio/historyrepeating_7olLrex.wav, skipping download.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "\n",
       "                <audio  controls=\"controls\" >\n",
       "                    <source src=\"data:audio/mpeg;base64,\" type=\"audio/mpeg\" />\n",
       "                    Your browser does not support the audio element.\n",
       "                </audio>\n",
       "              "
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.lib.display.Audio object>"

    "import nussl\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import time \n",
    "\n",
    "start_time = time.time()\n",
    "\n",
    "audio_path = nussl.efz_utils.download_audio_file('historyrepeating_7olLrex.wav')\n",
    "history = nussl.AudioSignal(audio_path)\n",
    "history.embed_audio()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 3))\n",
    "nussl.utils.visualize_spectrogram(history)\n",
    "plt.title(str(history))\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Neat. Now, we need to instantiate a ``Repet`` object. **Like all source separation algorithms** in *nussl*, ``Repet``\n",
    "needs an `AudioSignal` object as its first parameter when we initialize it.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "repet = nussl.separation.primitive.Repet(history)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Like all other algorithms in** *nussl*, ``Repet`` **has made its own copy of our** ``history`` object that it\n",
    "will manipulate, so we can reuse ``history`` again if we want to. Any modifications made on the signal passed to ``Repet`` will be done on a *copy* of ``history``.\n",
    "\n",
    "Repeating Period\n",
    "----------------\n",
    "\n",
    "If we know exactly what the repeating period is, we can give that ``Repet`` or if we kind of know where it is we can\n",
    "give it some estimates. Say I think the repeating period is about 3.5 seconds.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "repet_exact_period = nussl.separation.primitive.Repet(\n",
    "    history, period=3.5)  # exact period\n",
    "repet_period_guess = nussl.separation.primitive.Repet(\n",
    "    history, min_period=3.4, max_period=3.6)  # guess the period"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "But! If we have no clue, then ``Repet`` will try to find the repeating period for \n",
    "us, automatically. So we're back to this:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "repet = nussl.separation.primitive.Repet(history)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Running Repet\n",
    "-------------\n",
    "\n",
    "Now, we can run the algorithm, and **all nussl algorithms**, in a few ways. \n",
    "Every *nussl* algorithm has two important functions:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. `run()`\n",
    "2. `make_audio_signals()`\n",
    "\n",
    "The first one runs all of the necessary things to make the algorithm work. \n",
    "If it's a masking-based algorithm, then `run()` returns a list of `SoftMask` \n",
    "or `BinaryMask` objects. The second actually creates the audio signals that \n",
    "correspond to the separated sources.\n",
    "\n",
    "But if we do `make_audio_signals` before doing `run`, this happens:"
   ]
  },
  {
